  "body": "<!-- Briefly describe the issue you're experiencing. Tell us what you were trying to do and what happened instead. -->\r\n\r\nHaving a linting issue in ERC777.sol related to the length of one of the error messages.\r\n\r\n**üíª Environment**\r\nAll\r\n\r\n<!-- Tell us what version of OpenZeppelin Contracts you're using, and how you're using it: Truffle, Remix, etc. -->\r\nCurrent master branch\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n\r\n<!-- Describe the problem you have been experiencing in more detail. Include as much information as you think is relevant. Keep in mind that transactions can fail for many reasons; context is key here. -->\r\n\r\nLint is reporting the error message is too long for line 472 of ERC777.sol\r\n\r\n```\r\nrequire(!to.isContract(), \"ERC777: token recipient contract has no implementer for ERC777TokensRecipient\");\r\n```\r\nExact message is \r\n>\"error-reason: Error message exceeds max length of 76 characters\"\r\n\r\nFix is to shorten the error message to something like...\r\n```\r\nrequire(!to.isContract(), \"ERC777: token recipient missing ERC777TokensRecipient\");\r\n```",
